Master of Science in Information Systems

The Master of Science in Information Systems (MSIS) program at the University of Maryland is designed to prepare students for leadership roles in the rapidly evolving field of information technology and systems.

Program Overview

Our MSIS program combines technical expertise with business acumen, preparing graduates to bridge the gap between technology and business strategy. The curriculum is designed to provide students with a comprehensive understanding of information systems, data analytics, cybersecurity, and enterprise architecture.

Key Features

Flexible Learning Options

Choose between full-time and part-time study options to accommodate your schedule. Classes are offered in both traditional and online formats.

Learn More View Schedule

Industry Connections

Benefit from our strong partnerships with leading technology companies and organizations, providing networking opportunities and real-world project experiences.

Our Partners Success Stories

Expert Faculty

Learn from experienced professionals and researchers who bring real-world expertise and cutting-edge knowledge to the classroom.

Meet Faculty Research Areas

Career Support

Access comprehensive career services, including resume reviews, interview preparation, and job placement assistance through our dedicated career development office.

Career Services Job Board

Curriculum

Our curriculum is designed to provide a strong foundation in information systems while allowing students to specialize in areas such as:

  • Data Analytics and Business Intelligence
  • Cybersecurity and Information Assurance
  • Enterprise Architecture and Cloud Computing
  • Project Management and IT Governance
  • User Experience and Interface Design

Admission Requirements

To be considered for admission to the MSIS program, applicants must have:

  • A bachelor's degree from an accredited institution
  • Minimum GPA of 3.0 (on a 4.0 scale)
  • GRE or GMAT scores (waivers available for qualified applicants)
  • Professional resume and statement of purpose
  • Letters of recommendation
